   ALSO READ:ARCHBISHOP DIED A STRESSED MAN! With rainy weather in Cape Town, officials are seen arriving under umbrellas as they come to pay their last respects to the struggle icon. Among those who have arrived so far include president Cyril Ramaphosa, acting chief justice Raymond Zondo, Graca Machel, Mondli Gungubele, and former President Thabo Mbeki among others.   Tutu passed away in Cape Town on 26 December  at the age of 90. Tutu has been granted a special official funeral category This week, Archbishop of the Anglican Cape Town diocese Thabo Makgoba said the final resting place of Tutu will be inside the  St Georges Cathedral where his ashes will be interred. After the funeral a private cremation will take place.    